com.google.errorprone.annotations

注释类型 CanIgnoreReturnValue


  • @Target(value={METHOD,TYPE})
 @Retention(value=CLASS)
public @interface CanIgnoreReturnValue
    Indicates that the return value of the annotated method can be safely ignored.

    This is the opposite of javax.annotation.CheckReturnValue. It can be used inside classes or packages annotated with @CheckReturnValue to exempt specific methods from the default.
